Section 23.1326 Pitot Heat Indication System



Proposed new  23.1326 would require the installation of a pitot tube heat indicating system on those airplanes
required to be equipped with a heated pitot tube. Heated pitot tubes ensure that moisture will not freeze in the tube
and block or partially block the airspeed indicating system. Such blockage would result in the pilots receiving incorrect
flight data with possibly disastrous results.

