19. A new  23.855 is added to read as follows:


 23.855 

Cargo and baggage compartment fire protection.


(a) Sources of heat within each cargo and baggage compartment that are capable of igniting the compartment contents
must be shielded and insulated to prevent such ignition.
(b) Each cargo and baggage compartment must be constructed of materials that meet the appropriate provisions of  23.853(d)(3).
